            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I ran across this while working on the downstream SageMath ticket https://trac.sagemath.org/ticket/25633. My workaround was to use the old-style `for` syntax to generate the simple C code.\r\n\r\nFor the `step` that cannot be determined at compile time (such as an unsigned `int`), perhaps doing `for i in range(start, stop, step)` mapping to\r\n```c\r\nfor(i=start, (step > 0 && i < stop) || (step < 0 && i > stop), i+=step)\r\n```\r\nWhile it is not optimal, the extra comparison tests should be quick (if the C compiler does not optimize them away).",
            "created_at": "2019-01-04T20:12:09Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/532#issuecomment-451555455",
